==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Humanly
<hw>Hu"man*ly</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>In a human manner;
after the manner of men; according to the knowledge or wisdom of men;
<as>as, the present prospects, <ex>humanly</ex> speaking, promise a
happy issue</as>.</def> <rj><au>Sir W. Raleigh.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Kindly; humanely.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Pope.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Humanness</ent>⟦br⟧
